      "content": {
        "title": "Spina Bifida and Myelomeningocele — Orthopaedic Management — Core Principles",
        "definition": "Congenital neural tube defects causing paralytic deformities of the lower extremities requiring bracing and corrective surgery.",
        "summary": "Hip dislocation and equinovarus foot are common. Ambulatory potential depends on neurologic level. Late spinal deformity requires fusion."
      },
